******
[3] Montana
Date: 24 Aug 2018
Source: The Horse
https://thehorse.com/160131/wnv-in-montana-horses-additional-cases-confirmed/


The Equine Disease Communication Center (EDCC) reported on 23 Aug 2018 that the Montana Department of Livestock has confirmed additional cases of West Nile virus (WNV) in horses in that state. They've confirmed WNV in Montana horses residing in Blaine, Cascade, Lewis and Clark, Powder River, Wheatland, and Yellowstone counties.

The EDCC said cases include:

On 7 Aug 2018, one case was confirmed in Cascade County;
On 14 Aug 2018, one case each was confirmed in Lake and Cascade Counties;
On 15 Aug 2018, one case was confirmed in Cascade County;
On 16 Aug 2018, 2 cases were confirmed in Cascade County, and one was confirmed in Powder River County;
On 17 Aug 2018, one case each was confirmed in Blaine, Wheatland, and Cascade Counties;
On 20 Aug 2018, one case was confirmed in Lewis and Clark County; and
On 21 Aug 2018, 5 cases were confirmed, 3 in Cascade County, one in Lewis and Clark County, and one in Yellowstone County.

Previously, the Department of Livestock confirmed 2 cases of WNV in Montana horses: one in Lake County and one in Musselshell County. The newly reported cases bring the state's total to 18 cases of WNV in Montana horses so far this year [2018].

WNV has no cure; however, some horses can recover with supportive care. Equine mortality rates can reach 30-40 percent.

[Byline: Erica Larson]

