[What a pity horses die of a disease when there is a very effective vaccine. There are effective sprays specifically designed to control mosquitoes on horses.

Mosquitoes can be in almost any place. There is likely no place safe from this disease because of mosquitoes. Protect yourself from mosquitoes with repellant, wearing long sleeves and avoiding dawn and dusk.

People are also susceptible to WNV from mosquitoes, and some people remain asymptomatic. People who are bitten by an infected mosquito may not even realize they have contracted the disease. However, some people will feel ill with a fever, headaches and body aches within a few days or perhaps weeks after being bitten by an infected mosquito. On rare occasions, it can become a serious disease, and in some cases, it may become a neurological disease.

Provide your animals with the same thoughtful protection -- a vaccine and mosquito repellant -- and eliminate mosquito breeding places.

There is a vaccine for horses to help prevent them from contracting WNV, along with other equine diseases stemming from mosquito bites, but there is no such vaccine for people. - Mod.TG

